race.comment: ALIGNED (1) didn't have the clearest passage in the straight so his effort to be beaten just 1.1 lengths first-up over 1300m at Newcastle had merit. Won his only race when second-up over today's course and distance. Looks a terrific chance to break through despite 61kgs after a string of minor placings. HARRY'S EVIDENCE (4) started at a very short quote when successful recently in a maiden over this distance at Wyong. That followed a 24-week spell so there should be plenty of improvement to come. ANDREA (9) has been kept fresh since a close second over this distance at Port Macquarie five weeks ago. Up in class but drops sharply in the weights so worth considering. CLASSIC POCKET (3) was plain last time but is lightly raced and can do better. MISS FLEETWOOD (10) is not a noted first-up performer but a couple of strong recent trials suggest she is up for this.
